+# AWS Cognito — Configuration & Integration (dev / stage / prod)
+
+## Summary
+Canonical Cognito configuration and integration points for the Authentication MVP. Reference for Infra, Backend, and Mobile teams to create matching User Pools, App Clients, Hosted UI, IdP connections (Google, Apple), and email templates (SES).
+
+## Environments
+- dev: cognito-{project}-dev  
+- stage: cognito-{project}-stage  
+- prod: cognito-{project}-prod
+
+Each environment must have its own User Pool and App Clients or clear namespacing to avoid cross‑environment leakage.
+
+## User Pool — high level settings
+- Name pattern: {project}-user-pool-{env}  
+- Attributes:
+  - Required: email  
+  - Optional: given_name, family_name, phone_number  
+- Password policy:
+  - Minimum length: 8  
+  - Require: upper, lower, number, special (confirm with Security)  
+- Verification:
+  - Email verification via 6-digit numeric code  
+  - Verification code TTL: 10 minutes (configurable)  
+  - Max verification attempts per code: 5  
+- MFA: Disabled for MVP  
+- Account recovery: Email-based (enabled)
+
+## App Clients (per platform)
+1. **Mobile iOS client**  
+   - Name: {project}-ios-client-{env}  
+   - Grant types: Authorization code grant  
+   - PKCE: REQUIRED  
+   - Callback/Redirect URIs: app scheme(s) + hosted UI redirect  
+   - Client secret: DO NOT GENERATE for mobile
+
+2. **Mobile Android client**  
+   - Name: {project}-android-client-{env}  
+   - PKCE: REQUIRED  
+   - Redirect URIs: intent scheme + hosted UI redirect  
+   - Client secret: DO NOT STORE in app
+
+3. **Web client (server-side)**  
+   - Name: {project}-web-client-{env}  
+   - Grant types: Authorization code grant (server-side)  
+   - Client secret: allowed for server-side apps only  
+   - Redirect URIs: https://{domain}/auth/callback
+
+Common client settings:
+- access token expiration: 10–15 minutes (TBD)  
+- refresh token expiration: 7–30 days (TBD)  
+- id token expiration: 10–60 minutes (TBD)  
+- token revocation: enabled and documented
+
+## Hosted UI
+- Use Cognito hosted domain or custom domain if branding required.  
+- Strict redirect URI allowlist — no wildcards.  
+- Hosted UI flows used for SSO (Google, Apple) and email signin/signup.
+
+## Identity Providers (IdP)
+- **Google (OIDC)**  
+  - Create OAuth app in Google Console and supply client_id to Cognito  
+  - Map attributes: email → email, name → name  
+  - Scopes: openid email profile
+
+- **Apple Sign In**  
+  - Register Service ID and upload private key, set Team ID in Apple Developer  
+  - Configure in Cognito; handle email private relay cases
+
+## Email (SES) integration
+- Verify SES identities for dev/stage/prod  
+- Templates:
+  - verification_email_template (6-digit code)  
+  - password_reset_template (6-digit code)  
+- Sender address: no-reply@{domain} (verified)  
+- Configure DKIM/SPF and bounce/complaint handling
+
+## Security & Best Practices
+- Enforce PKCE for all native/mobile clients  
+- Do NOT store client_secret in mobile apps  
+- Validate state & nonce for OAuth flows  
+- Exact-match redirect URIs only  
+- Token storage:
+  - refresh_token: Keychain (iOS) / Keystore (Android)  
+  - access/id tokens: in-memory  
+- Token rotation & revoke: document policy  
+- Redact PII and token material from logs; audit auth events
+
+## Monitoring & Observability
+- Metrics to collect: registration success rate, email delivery, login success/failure per flow, token refresh failures, latency p95  
+- Alerts: auth error rate spike, SES bounce spike, PKCE callback errors
+
+## Testing / Validation (dev)
+- E2E: register→verify→login; forgot→reset→login; SSO Google/Apple; logout & GlobalSignOut; refresh token behavior  
+- Validate PKCE end‑to‑end; confirm email templates render and deliver
