+## Deployment strategy
+- Gate: feature flag `feature.auth.*` controls prod behavior. Perform staged rollout behind this flag: 5% → 25% → 50% → 100%. Do not proceed to next stage until verification window passes and metrics are healthy.
+
+## Metric thresholds / rollback triggers
+- Success goal during rollout windows:
+  - Error rate < 1% (auth failures excluding expected 4xx)  
+  - p95 latency < 500 ms (excluding external IdP latency)
+- Immediate rollback triggers:
+  - Error rate spike above 5% over 5–10 minutes  
+  - p95 latency > 500 ms sustained for 10+ minutes  
+  - Critical security incident (token leakage, exposed secret)  
+  - Major functional regression
+
+## Deployment steps — Staging
+1. Deploy candidate to staging.  
+2. Toggle `feature.auth.*` ON in staging (or subflags).  
+3. Run smoke tests (see /features/auth/testing.md).  
+4. Validate dashboards and metrics.  
+5. If issues — fix and redeploy.
+
+## Deployment steps — Production (canary → full)
+1. Pre‑deploy checks green; stakeholders notified.  
+2. Deploy code & infra changes to production.  
+3. Set feature flag to Canary 5%. Document time & settings.  
+4. Wait verification window: 15–30 minutes. Monitor metrics and run smoke tests.  
+5. If OK → increase to 25% (30–60 minutes).  
+6. If OK → increase to 50% (60 minutes).  
+7. If OK → increase to 100%.  
+8. If a rollback trigger fires → execute rollback procedure.
+
+## Smoke tests (manual + automated)
+- Use test accounts in Appendix A. For each window, run:
+  1. Register → receive code → verify → tokens issued  
+  2. Login with email/password  
+  3. Forgot password → receive code → reset → login  
+  4. Logout → GlobalSignOut → confirm refresh token invalidation  
+  5. Google SSO — Hosted UI end‑to‑end  
+  6. Apple Sign‑in — Hosted UI on iOS  
+  7. Token refresh flow  
+  8. Negative PKCE test
+
+Record timestamps, logs, and metric snapshots for each test.
+
+## Rollback procedure (fast)
+1. Toggle `feature.auth.*` OFF (or reduce exposure).  
+2. If code rollback needed, redeploy previous stable release.  
+3. If Cognito config change caused issue, revert configuration.  
+4. Inform stakeholders and open incident ticket.  
+5. SRE: capture logs, traces, and metrics for post‑mortem.
+
+## Post-rollback steps
+- Triage: Lead Dev + SRE + Security to analyze logs and reproduce in staging.  
+- Create Jira issues for root cause fixes.  
+- Re‑test in staging and only re‑schedule rollout after fixes validated.
+
+## Post-deploy validation & acceptance
+- Confirm smoke tests passed at 100% rollout.  
+- Confirm dashboards stable for 60 minutes post‑100% deployment.  
+- Security: no token leaks, no PII in logs.  
+- Update docs: record timestamps, decisions, and update /runbooks/deployment-auth.md with outcomes.
